On 01Feb2012 01:39, Paulo da Silva <p_s_d_a_s_i_l_v_a@netcabo.pt> wrote:
| What is the best way to iterate thru a huge list having the 1st element
| a different process? I.e.:
| 
| process1(mylist[0])
| for el in mylist[1:]:
| 	process2(el)
| 
| This way mylist is almost duplicated, isn't it?

Yep.

What about (untested):

  process1(mylist[0])
  for i in xrange(1,len(mylist)):
  	process2(mylist[i])

